<br>
The primary reason I am on VZ is not because I can loot gear off of other players.  It is because everyone else can.  The reason that I think that this is a good thing, is because without item loot, you have twinks. If you remove item loot, you go from having naked casters (cheeseballs) having the advantage to fully twinked out characters(cheeseballs) having the advantage. *Some one* will always have the advantage. Being able to loot some one's hard-earned spellbook is a hell of a way to avoid the naked caster syndrome and still maintain the item loot rules.  Then *everyone* would use their best gear, and everyone would very carefully consider attacking before they attacked.  <br>
<br>
As it is now, people do not wear gear that they cannot hold.  If I see a lvl 8 DE rogue all decked out in RS armor, you better believe that I'm gonna kill him once every hour until he either puts the stuff up, or I have a full set, which I will then bank and keep until I am high enough level to defend my prize.  You *do* see lvl 35 rogues all in RS... you *should*.  They are high enough level to go to CT and get it.  By then, they are of such a level that it would be less risky for a naked caster to put on his gear and go to CT and get it himself than try to take out that rogue and his friends.<br>
<br>
I have not played on VZ for very long.  My highest level character on the server is only lvl 11, but I get the feeling that most of the kvetching is comming from people who just are either just too lazy to think of good tactics to use in PVP, or have made it all the way into the 40s and 50s, and want to be able to twink their newbie character.<br>
<br>
I Hate naked casters.  I hate Twinks more.  By virtue of my being a Shank, it goes without saying that I hate xteaming too, but it is something I am willing to deal with.  Non-humans are all the same in Plumber's eyes, and there will always be misguided collaborators out there.  If something can be done about xteaming, great, but otherwise, LEAVE VZ ALONE!<br>
<br>
Eric Stevenson, Player<br>
